name: sfchronicle
text: A day after reporting a record 410 new cases, Santa Clara County recorded 313 new cases on Sunday — still a high total for the county, where daily new cases have rarely been above 300 in recent weeks. https://t.co/UNWfCZdMRj

text:
Pianist Leon Fleisher, sidelined but never defeated by injury, is dead at 92.

Obituary by @JoshuaKosman: https://t.co/wyCzhjpeAj

name: sfchronicle
text: RT @SportingGreenSF: Amid the looming threat that baseball could be shut down because of the sport’s coronavirus outbreak, the @SFGiants are hitting the road for their longest trip of the season, writes @JohnSheaHey. https://t.co/oTnQWRQnDq

name: sfchronicle
text: Two San Quentin inmates die, likely due to COVID-19: Orlando Romero, 48, died Sunday. Officials say it appears to be from complications related to COVID-19. A second inmate died Sunday, bringing the total number of deaths there due to coronavirus to 21. https://t.co/oOtoNXpDES

name: sfchronicle
text:
A four-block stretch of the Tenderloin will be remodeled to make room for pedestrians, a temporary project intended to allow for more physical distancing during the coronavirus pandemic.

Story by @MeganRCassidy: https://t.co/NzoFoXtoHi
